    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-14T01:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-14T01:30:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">390.1115A/959: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Calcutta</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schnare</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Calcutta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-14T12:00:00+05:30"
                            >July 14, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>506. Your 301, July 3, 9 p.m. Estimate resident Americans now desiring
                    transportation between two and three hundred. VG<note n="47" xml:id="d212fn47"
                        >American Volunteer Group.</note> and convalescent Army personnel may add
                    about 200. Further Allied reverses may increase evacuation resident Americans.
                    Please advise what shipping facilities arranged.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schnare</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
